{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nThe two model sub-questions (containment, layer) must be calibrated so suppression never hides a\nsevere / cross-sibling / delivered-functionality / security finding. Per G-Eval, freeze wording and\ncalibrate to a gold set (kappa ~0.8) whose anchors are the must-never-suppress cases.\n\n## What\n\nBuild a gold-set fixture + an end-to-end partially-complete-epic review test. The gold set encodes\nlabelled findings: pure re-litigation (drop) vs must-never-suppress anchors — a delivered child's\ndelivered-functionality/security finding, a finding spanning an open sibling, a finding on a\nforce-closed child, and a delivered child that opened a security boundary. Add the calibration\nrecord under `docs/calibration/` (a LIVE run, since the changed artifact is a prompt) and the test\nmodule under `tests/plan_review/`.\n\n## Scope\n\n- IN: the gold-set fixture; the end-to-end partially-complete-epic test; the calibration doc.\n- OUT: the floor/predicate/sub-call implementations (their own stories).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A gold-set fixture labels drop vs must-never-suppress findings, including the four anchor cases above.\n- [ ] An end-to-end test builds a partially-complete epic (delivered + open + force-closed children) and asserts: delivered plan-semantics findings dropped; delivered-functionality/security, cross-sibling, and force-closed-child findings preserved.\n- [ ] A calibration record (LIVE LLM run) is written under `docs/calibration/` reporting agreement against the gold set.\n- [ ] The suite runs green with the completion floor active and is byte-identical with it inactive.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria (ordering + invariants)\n\n- [ ] Calibration runs only AFTER 94fd's prompt is frozen (explicit `depends_on` 94fd); a later prompt revision retriggers recalibration (the calibration record notes the prompt hash it was run against).\n- [ ] A non-regression test asserts the epic's success-criteria invariants: NO `close`-operation change, NO new attestation kind, and code-drift / fire-timing invalidation unchanged (only what a re-fired review DOES changes).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria (gold-set scope)\n\n- [ ] The gold-set has >=5 labelled cases per anchor category (pure re-litigation -> drop; delivered-functionality -> keep; security/contract T5c/T10 -> keep; cross-sibling spans-open -> keep; force-closed child -> keep), >=25 total, and 'complete' = every category represented across the G3/G4, coherence, and overlay criterion provenances.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria (reopen invariant)\n\n- [ ] A test covers the reopened-child auto-resurface invariant: a delivered child whose findings were dropped, once reopened, is no longer `delivered-now` (recomputed that run) so its findings resurface — asserting the recompute-every-run / no-persisted-drop behaviour end to end."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782976316307907001,"uuid":"c0de12bc-18f9-46bf-bdf9-f1f4c4783f15"}